-- Spanish Buy-to-Let Homes Yield Higher Returns Than Paris, Berlin
-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 2012-01-24T11:28:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-24/spanish-buy-to-let-homes-yield-higher-returns-than-paris-berlin.html
Buy-to-let homes in Madrid and
 Barcelona  offer investors higher yields than similar properties
in Paris or Berlin, according to  study  by  Idealista.com ,  Spain ’s
largest property  website .  Homes for rent in Madrid and Barcelona, Spain’s two largest
cities, offer gross annual yields of 4.1 percent and 3.9
percent, respectively, whereas similar properties in Paris and
Berlin offer yields of offer 3.3 percent and 3.7 percent,
Idealista said today in an e-mailed statement.  Buy-to-let homes in London and  Rome  offer the highest
yields in  Europe  at 4.3 percent and 4.5 percent, respectively,
according to the study.  Gross annual yields were calculated by dividing the average
sales prices of properties across Europe by average annual
rental income, Idealista said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid  at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
